The paper deals with entity retrieval, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses various methods for constructing vector spaces from text sequences, which is a common topic in natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the ability of expert representations to encode academic rank, which is a topic in social informatics (cs.SI).
